&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Education Lead &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;£44,000 - £48,000 per year (pro rata) &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bray Lake, Maidenhead &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;22.5 hours per week &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports to:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Director of Education and Innovation &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsible for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Education Office Administrator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fantastic opportunity to work at Thames Hospice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with the Director of Education and Innovation you will develop and lead an aspirational programme of learning that is recognised in the sector and beyond, as being both innovative and relevant in meeting the current and future needs locally and nationally. You will support the development of a competent and confident hospice workforce by providing/facilitating effective learning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful you will need to be passionate about end of life/palliative care issues and be keen to see whole system change, alongside the development of services and professionals involved in their delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Appointment is subject to an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service check including barred lists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like an informal discussion about this role, please contact Linda Freeman, Director of Education and Innovation via e-mail &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;linda.freeman@thameshospice.org.uk&lt;/span&gt; or call01753 848965&lt;/p&gt;
